{
  "stem": "21310.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father, I know, had one friend that I am going to talk about him a little later.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was a strong, Polish patriot.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, but he-- he used to spend many evenings with my father playing chess.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I had some non-Jewish friends and some Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Although when I walked to school in elementary school, there were-- sometimes some young kids would yell, 'Dirty Jew!' And I do know that whenever there was a soccer game, when it emptied, when-- after the soccer game, we didn't go into the street.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were afraid because the-- all the-- somehow the soccer fans were always very rambunctious and noisy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And somehow they always started with anti-Semitic remarks or yelling.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And also, at Easter time when we-- we were usually afraid because people coming out from the church frequently didn't like-- you know, said something against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But in my early years, I didn't hear too much, didn't have too much anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I did attend first a public school where [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there were prayers every morning, and the Jewish kids just had to stand.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we didn't take part in prayers when the priest came.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They would have a-- at the same time, they would have a teacher come and teach us Jewish history, more modern religion.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father hired a halutz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It's a young man who was preparing to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was in the Hachsharah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he taught me Hebrew as a living language.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So later on, I-- and-- my father-- from fourth grade on, I went to a private Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the schools were-- girls went to school separately.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was-- it was segregated.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
